results.deck: Stormfront studios was an American game developer company founded in 1988 which closed down in 2008.
results.description: Initially named Beyond Software (from 1991 to 1993), Stormfront Studios was founded in 1988 by Don Daglow of former Broderbund software fame. Their most successful released included the children's edutainment adventure series Eagle Eye mysteries, the NASCAR series published by EA, Stronghold and numerous Lord of The Rings games (based on the movies rather than the books) The company closed on March 31st, 2008 after failing to secure a publisher for its internal project.
